org.ndnx.ndn.protocol
Class Exclude

java.lang.Object
  org.ndnx.ndn.impl.encoding.GenericXMLEncodable
      org.ndnx.ndn.protocol.Exclude
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<Exclude>, XMLEncodable
public class Exclude
extends GenericXMLEncodable
implements XMLEncodable, Comparable<Exclude>

Exclude filters are used during Interest matching to exclude content. The filter works on the name component after the last one specified in the Interest. Exclude filters contain at least one element. The elements are either a name component, a bloom filter or the 'any' element. This allows the specification of individual component values to be excluded, as well as arbitrary ranges of component values and a compact form for long lists of component values (bloom filters). The order of elements within an exclude filter must follow 2 rules: 1. Within an exclude filter all name component elements must be in ascending order wherever they occur and there should be no duplicates. 2. An any element or a bloom filter element must not be followed by an any element or bloom filter.

See Also:
I.E. Any elements or bloom filters must be separated by at least one name component element.
